'''Francisco Cruz Castro''' (4 October 1820 in [[Santa Ana, El Salvador]] &ndash; 20 May 1895 in [[La Esperanza, Honduras]]) was a [[El Salvador|Salvadoran]]-born [[Honduras|Honduran]] doctor, lawyer, politician and diplomat. He was [[Minister of Government]] from 1844-1846, Magistrate of the [[Superior Court of Justice (Brazil)|Superior Tribunal of Justice]] from 1850-1852, [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Honduras)|Minister of Foreign Relations]] from 1856-1858 and [[President of Honduras|Provisional President of Honduras]] from September 5, 1869 to January 14, 1870.<ref>{{cite book|title=El Libro de Honduras: directorio y guía general de la República. The book of Honduras; directory and general guide of the country|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6PRkAAAAMAAJ|year=1958|publisher=Tipografia Nacional|language=Spanish|page=39}}</ref>

