A '''priesthood blessing''' in [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] (LDS Church) is a "prayer for healing, comfort or counsel given by a [[Melchizedek priesthood (Latter Day Saints)|Melchizedek Priesthood]] holder, who lays his hands on the head of the person receiving the blessing."<ref>{{Citation |title= Helpful Words to Know |journal= [[Ensign (LDS magazine)|Ensign]] |date=October 2006 |url= http://www.lds.org/ensign/2006/10/helpful-words-to-know?lang=eng |publisher= LDS Church }}</ref> Priesthood blessings are considered to be non-saving [[Ordinance (Latter Day Saints)|ordinances]] by Latter-day Saints.<ref>{{citation |first= Dallin H. |last= Oaks |authorlink= Dallin H. Oaks |date=May 1987 |title= Priesthood Blessings |journal= Ensign |url= http://www.lds.org/ensign/1987/05/priesthood-blessings?lang=eng }}</ref>

